OL,3,CFire boss resignation accepted after
OL,4,Cattempted withdrawal
OL,6,FCllr Catherine Miks, Vice Chair of the
OL,7,FFire Authority, chaired the meeting
OL,8,Ffollowing Brackenridge's recent
OL,9,Fresignation.
OL,11,FIn her statement, Miks said:
OL,12,F"Following Oliver's resignation last
OL,13,Fweek, it was necessary for the Fire
OL,14,FAuthority to accept or decline his
OL,15,Fresignation.
OL,17,F"Based on independent legal and
OL,18,Femployment advice, the Fire Authority
OL,19,Fhas made the decision to accept
OL,20,FOliver's resignation with immediate
OL,21,Feffect."
